  <h2>Best Practices Implemented</h2>
  <ol style="color:#a0a0c0;font-size:13px;line-height:2">
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">IIFE Module Pattern</strong> — Zero global leakage</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Defensive DOM</strong> — Every operation checks <code>if (el)</code> before access</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Error Boundaries</strong> — <code>try/catch</code> wrapping all init paths</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Memory Safety</strong> — All timers, listeners, and observers have cleanup methods</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Null-Safe Chains</strong> — No "Cannot read property of null" crashes</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Graceful Degradation</strong> — localStorage fails ? memory fallback</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">API Resilience</strong> — 3 encoding fallbacks for cross-browser compatibility</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Separation of Concerns</strong> — Core / Components / Patterns / Services / App</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Single Responsibility</strong> — Each file &lt; 120 lines, one clear purpose</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Platform-Aware</strong> — <code>env(safe-area-inset-bottom)</code> for notched devices</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Accessibility</strong> — <code>role="dialog"</code>, <code>aria-modal</code>, focus trap, keyboard nav</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">Touch Targets</strong> — All interactive elements = 44px (Apple HIG)</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">CSS Variables</strong> — Theming via <code>var(--blue)</code> for consistent dark/light modes</li>
    <li><strong style="color:#fff">No Framework Lock-In</strong> — Pure vanilla JS, composable, testable in any stack</li>
  </ol>


